      <div class="samsung-pricing-context">
        <p class="samsung-context-paragraph">Samsung repair costs are primarily driven by the screen - OEM Samsung AMOLED displays for flagship S series and Z series devices can be surprisingly expensive, often comparable to iPhone screen repairs. <a href="https://www.samsung.com/ca/support/service-center/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="samsung-context-link">Samsung provides official guidance on device care and battery maintenance</a> that can help extend the lifespan of your Galaxy phone before a repair becomes necessary.</p>
        <p class="samsung-context-paragraph">Many customers expect Samsung repairs to cost less than iPhone repairs, but premium AMOLED screens for Galaxy S Ultra and Z Fold models often cost the same or more due to the display technology involved. <a href="https://www.ifixit.com/Search?query=samsung+galaxy+repair" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="samsung-context-link">iFixit's Samsung teardowns</a> illustrate why - foldable devices like the Z Fold and Z Flip have particularly complex internal assemblies that significantly affect repair difficulty and cost.</p>
        <p class="samsung-context-paragraph">If the repair cost approaches your Galaxy's current market value, we'll tell you clearly and walk you through alternatives - including trade-in options toward a newer device or a refurbished Samsung from our pre-owned inventory.</p>
