  <section class="samsung-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="samsung-container">
      <div class="samsung-section-header">
        <h2 class="samsung-section-title">Samsung Galaxy Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="samsung-section-subtitle">Common questions about Samsung repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="samsung-faq-list">
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does Samsung Galaxy screen replacement take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">Most Samsung Galaxy screen replacements are completed in 1-2 hours at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. Galaxy Z Fold and Z Flip foldable devices may take 2-4 hours due to their complex inner display and hinge assemblies.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Samsung Galaxy Z Fold and Z Flip in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">Yes - we're one of the few Winnipeg repair shops with genuine experience servicing Samsung Z Fold and Z Flip foldables including inner screen, outer screen, hinge mechanism, and flex cable repairs. Contact us before visiting to confirm parts availability for your specific model and generation.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>How much does Samsung Galaxy repair cost in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">Samsung repair costs vary significantly by model - Galaxy A series repairs are generally the most straightforward, while flagship S series and foldable Z series cost more due to premium AMOLED and foldable display components. Contact us or use our online quote tool for a free upfront price on your specific model.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you use genuine Samsung parts for repairs?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">We use high-quality parts that meet or exceed OEM specifications, and OEM Samsung displays are available for models where aftermarket screens cannot be reliably warrantied. We discuss part options and pricing with you before starting any repair so you can choose the level that fits your budget.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Will I lose my data during Samsung Galaxy repair?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">For most repairs including screen, battery, and charging port, your data remains completely intact. We recommend backing up your Galaxy before any repair as a precaution - for water damage cases, data recovery is prioritised and we document the device state on arrival.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Samsung Galaxy water damage in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">Yes - despite IP ratings, Samsung Galaxy phones can still suffer liquid damage from salt water, pool chemicals, or older models with degraded seals. We perform ultrasonic cleaning and component-level diagnostics to assess what can be recovered - bring it in as soon as possible for the best outcome.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Samsung Galaxy cameras in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">Yes - we repair all Galaxy camera modules including the 200MP main sensor on Galaxy S24 Ultra, periscope telephoto lenses on Pro models, and front selfie cameras across all Galaxy generations. Camera repairs restore full resolution, optical zoom, and video recording quality.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix a Samsung Galaxy that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">Yes - a non-responsive Galaxy is often caused by a depleted battery, a failed display connection, or a software boot issue. We run free diagnostics to identify the root cause before recommending any repair so you know exactly what the problem is before spending anything.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Do I need an appointment for Samsung repair in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">No appointment is needed - walk-ins are welcome at both our St. Vital and Thompson locations during business hours. Calling ahead is helpful for Z Fold or Z Flip repairs so we can confirm parts availability and give you an accurate time estimate before your visit.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="samsung-faq-item">
          <summary class="samsung-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Samsung Galaxy phones in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="samsung-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="samsung-faq-answer">Yes - our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts Samsung Galaxy repairs Monday through Saturday 10AM-6PM. We stock parts for common Galaxy A and S series models - calling ahead helps confirm availability for Z Fold, Z Flip, or newer flagship models.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

